        "title": "[codex] keep Gmail label IDs case-sensitive",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- keep Gmail label ID handling case-sensitive during label resolution\n- prefer exact case-sensitive label IDs before case-insensitive label-name lookup\n- keep duplicate-name preflight from case-folding label IDs while still blocking exact ID/name collisions\n\n## Root cause\n\nGmail label resolution built a single lowercase lookup map for both label names and label IDs. That made custom label IDs behave case-insensitively even though Gmail IDs are opaque case-sensitive tokens, and it also made exact IDs vulnerable to case-folded label-name shadowing unless exact IDs are checked first.\n\n## Validation\n\n- go test ./internal/cmd -run 'TestEnsureLabelNameAvailable|TestResolveLabelIDs|TestGmailLabelsGetCmd_ExactIDBeatsCaseFoldedName|TestFetchLabelNameToID'\n- make test\n- live test with clawdbot@gmail.com: created temp Gmail label `Label_18`, exact `gmail labels get Label_18` succeeded, lowercased `gmail labels get label_18` failed as expected, temp label deleted, cleanup check found `tmp_label_leftovers:0`\n- /Users/steipete/Projects/agent-scripts/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local\n",
